      "side": 1,
      "message": "Since self can also refer to a comprehension body (which is syntactically a struct), consider wording that covers it, e.g. \"refer to the innermost struct, list, or comprehension body, or the top level if none exist\". As written, \"innermost struct or list\" invites reading self inside `[for x in l {...}]` as referring to the enclosing list, when it actually refers to the yielded element.",
      "revId": "bdf21e755ecb6680d05a8bf777ef3a8d7f7be835",
