      "side": 1,
      "message": "Worth adding comprehension examples here. The comprehension body is a struct, so self can refer to it:\n\n```\n// comprehension bodies\nj: [ for x in [1, 2] { v: x, w: self.v } ] // refers to each yielded element\nk: {\n    n: 1\n    for _ in [1] { m: self.n } // body embeds into k, so refers to value of k (1)\n}\n```\n\nIn the list case the body is the yielded element, so self does not reach the enclosing list; in the field case the body embeds into the enclosing struct, so self observably refers to that struct.",
      "revId": "bdf21e755ecb6680d05a8bf777ef3a8d7f7be835",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
